  * Showcase your Solution Architecture expertise within our innovative environment 
  * Collaborate with business, IT stakeholders and the broader Architecture community 
  * Brisbane, Sydney, Melbourne location, flexibility the Suncorp way! 

We’re never just satisfied with how things are – because we know how things
could be. And it’s our expert Technology team who forge ahead every day to
make those ‘what ifs’ a reality.

Welcome to a place where you can chase real progress and drive real change.
And that includes your own career. Being a part of Technology at Suncorp Group
means being switched on, endlessly curious and always adaptable. In return,
you’ll be supported to bring your own ideas to the table and challenge
conventions – with the aim of making life a little brighter, simpler, and
better for our customers and each other.

Are you ready to join a dynamic team of collaborative and energetic
professionals? As a Solution Architect, you'll have the exciting opportunity
to define and deliver cutting-edge technology solutions that align with our
business and IT strategies. Your role will be crucial in shaping our projects
while adhering to best practices and industry standards. In this position, you
will work closely with our Corporate Platform team providing specialised
Solution Architecture expertise related to Corporate products and services for
People & Culture, Risk, Legal, Procurement and Finance.

This is a terrific opportunity to be part of a fun and innovative environment
where your contributions will make a significant impact!

** What you’ll do **

  * Define current, transition, and target state solution architectures in line with domain and group architecture 
  * Design for reuse and deployment across the group, leveraging existing components and infrastructure 
  * Ensure implementable solutions within business risk parameters, with a focus on performance, scalability, and security compliance 
  * Prepare solution designs and solutions options to support delivery 
  * Actively monitor project compliance with architecture and champion solution designs when necessary 
  * Review system designs to ensure they adhere to applicable strategies and/or solution architecture, while still considering business pragmatism and cost 
  * Provide overall technical leadership to agile teams in terms of the end-to-end solution, ensuring all facets of the designs and technologies are integrated to deliver an architecturally compliant implementation 

** **

** What you’ll bring **

  * Bachelor Degree in Information Technology or related disciplines, or equivalent experience 
  * Architectural certification (e.g., TOGAF or other) desired 
  * Minimum 5 years of IT experience 
  * Minimum 3 years of IT Architecture or Design experience 
  * Experience with HCM and Oracle Cloud Platform and products highly desirable 
  * Experience in integration solutions such as Mulesoft, Pentaho and Oracle Integration Cloud 
  * Familiarity with ArchiMate desired 
  * Experience with Agile & Lean methodologies desired 
  * Insurance or Financial services experience desired 

** What we can offer you **

  * Competitive benefits package and excellent work culture 
  * Excellent discounts on a range of retail favourite stores as well as banking and insurance products 
  * A range of flexible working and leave options, including 20 weeks paid parental leave and unlimited paid emergency response leave 
  * Invest in your brighter future with ongoing study support and career development programs 

